<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-08-16T10:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-08-16T10:30:00-05:00" n="218" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d218">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">833.34/77: Telegram</note>
                                <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Uruguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Montevideo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-08-16T12:00:00-03:30">August 16, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 12:31
                                        p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>183. Your air mail despatch 119 of August 6<note n="40" xml:id="d218fn1">Not printed.</note> made no mention of the
                                    Uruguayan request concerning possibility of buying destroyers
                                    (see my despatch No. 398, July 1<note n="40" xml:id="d218fn2">Not printed.</note>). Please telegraph what I can reply to
                                    the Uruguayan Government.</p>
                                <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi></signed></closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>